<TITLE> Iftekhar leaves for Japan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 24 (bdnews24.com)Foreign affairs adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury Sunday left for Japan on a four-day official visit, the foreign ministry said in a statement. During his stay, the adviser will meet his Japanese counterpart Masahiko Koumura who invited Iftekhar to visit Japan. The adviser will sign a deal on a Japanese loan of $60 million for "Emergency Disaster Damage Rehabilitation Project, the statement said. Iftekhar will arrive back in Dhaka on the evening of Feb 28. bdn
